⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 28/120 – HAVING Condition

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to:

1. Calculate the total salary for each department.


2. Display only departments where the total salary is greater than 100000.




---

📊 Input Dataset

department	salary

IT	60000
HR	45000
IT	70000
Finance	55000
HR	48000



---

✅ Expected Output

department	total_salary

IT	130000



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import sum, col

df.groupBy("department") \
  .agg(sum("salary").alias("total_salary")) \
  .filter(col("total_salary") > 100000) \
  .show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is the PySpark equivalent of SQL HAVING?

Answer

Filter after aggregation.

df.groupBy(...)
  .agg(...)
  .filter(...)


---

Q2. Can we use where() instead of filter()?

Answer

Yes.

where() and filter() are aliases in PySpark.


---

